<paragraph id="953E36FB272EA5701CD3FA280FF4FA77" blockId="3.[171,1190,1416,1438]" box="[171,1190,1416,1438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">
Рис. 2. 
<taxonomicName id="52814D78272EA5701C8AFA280ADCFA77" authority="Sergi &amp; Perkovsky, 2014" authorityName="Sergi &amp; Perkovsky" authorityYear="2014" box="[242,398,1416,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="usovae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE9272EA5701C8AFA280ADCFA77" box="[242,398,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">Latridius usovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BCC65792272EA5701DEBFA280A9AFA77" box="[403,456,1416,1438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="322" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE9272EA5701DA9FA280A8EFA77" box="[465,476,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">1</emphasis>
— вид сверху; 
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE9272EA5701E0EFA2809D3FA77" box="[630,641,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">2</emphasis>
— передняя нога; 
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE9272EA5701F47FA280818FA77" box="[831,842,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">3</emphasis>
— средняя нога; 
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE9272EA5701F83FA280F54FA77" box="[1019,1030,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">4</emphasis>
— задняя нога.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="953E36FB272EA5771C9BF9250A4BFEDB" blockId="3.[174,1231,1531,1835]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,175,930]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="323" pageId="3" pageNumber="322">
Legs moderately long and narrow. Trochanters obliquely truncate, about as long as broad. Femora spindle-shaped, thickened distally and 2.0–2.5 times as wide as tibiae; fore femur with longitudinal wrinkles on ventral surface. Tibiae thin, as long as femora; fore tibia feebly curved, 
<quantity id="52799B1E272EA5701E04F94D098FF8E1" box="[636,733,1773,1800]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="322" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long; mid tibia straight, 
<quantity id="52799B1E272EA570185DF94D0FD4F8E1" box="[1061,1158,1773,1800]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="322" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long, with big straight apical tooth as long as tarsomere 1; hind tibia slender, distinctly curved inwards, 
<quantity id="52799B1E2729A5771D05FF0F0ABFFF23" box="[381,493,175,202]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
long. Fore and mid tarsi about 2/3 as long as respective tibiae, hind tarsus about 2/5 as long as hind tibia; tarsomeres 1 and 2 equal in length; tarsomere 3 distinctly longer than both previous ones together. Claws simple, small and thin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="953E36FB2729A5771CA3FE9A0917FE91" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">E t y m o l o g y. The species named in honour of Professor Zinaida Usova (1924–2013), scientific adviser of the first author.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="953E36FB2729A5771CA3FEDF0A39FCF1" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
Comparison. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A5771F7FFE2008F5FE70" baseAuthorityName="Borowiec" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[775,935,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jantaricus">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A5771F7FFE2008F5FE70" box="[775,935,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L. jantaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the anterior angles of pronotum not projecting forward, lack of depressions at anterior angles of pronotum, shallow median longitudinal depression (
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A5771F6DFE6508E1FE37" baseAuthorityName="Borowiec" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[789,947,453,478]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jantaricus">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A5771F6DFE6508E1FE37" box="[789,947,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L. jantaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has anterior angles of pronotum moderately projecting forward, disc of pronotum with depression near middle of lateral margin and with deep median longitudinal depression); shorter elytra, lack of strong carinae on interstriae of elytra. 
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A5771F53FD8D08CDFDAF" authorityName="Sergi &amp; Perkovsky" authorityYear="2014" box="[811,927,557,582]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="usovae">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A5771F53FD8D08CDFDAF" box="[811,927,557,582]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L. usovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A577183EFD8D0F9AFDAF" authorityName="Bukejs, Kirejtshuk et Rucker" authorityYear="2011" box="[1094,1224,556,584]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexeevi">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A577183EFD8D0F04FDAF" box="[1094,1110,557,582]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A577181EFD8C0F9AFDAF" box="[1126,1224,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">alexeevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having anterior angles of pronotum not projecting forward, lacking depressions at anterior angles of pronotum (in 
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A5771E11FDD309BFFD65" authorityName="Bukejs, Kirejtshuk et Rucker" authorityYear="2011" box="[617,749,626,652]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexeevi">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A5771E11FDD309BFFD65" box="[617,749,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L. alexeevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
anterior angles of pronotum moderately projecting anteriorly, disc of pronotum with shallow depressions at anterior angles), and in having elytra about 1.3 times as long as wide (vs. about 1.5 times in 
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A5771CDEFD7B0A7AFD1D" authorityName="Bukejs, Kirejtshuk et Rucker" authorityYear="2011" box="[166,296,730,756]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexeevi">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A5771CDEFD7B0A7AFD1D" box="[166,296,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L. alexeevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species differs from both species by having hind tibia distinctly curved mesally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="953E36FB2729A5771CA3FCBF0F4BFC4B" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">
The new species is similar to the extant species 
<taxonomicName id="52814D782729A5771F50FC800FD1FCD3" authority="(Le Conte, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Le Conte" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[808,1155,799,826]" class="Insecta" family="Latridiidae" genus="Latridius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crenatus">
<emphasis id="A7F5EAE92729A5771F50FC8008F9FCD0" box="[808,939,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">L. crenatus</emphasis>
(Le Conte, 1855)
</taxonomicName>
from the western 
<collectingCountry id="ED96766B2729A5771D45FCE20AC5FCB4" box="[317,407,834,861]" name="Canada" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">Canada</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="ED96766B2729A5771DA1FCE20943FCB4" box="[473,529,834,861]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="323">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F1104B0A2729A5771E5CFCE209CCFCB4" author="Fall, H. C." box="[548,670,834,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" pagination="3 - 5" refId="ref2193" refString="Fall, H. C. Revision of the Lathridiidae of boreal America // Transactions of the American Entomological Society. - 1899. - 26. - P. 101 - 190 + pls. 3 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1899">Fall, 1899</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F1104B0A2729A5771ED5FCE20813FCB4" author="Hatch, M. H. The" box="[685,833,834,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="323" refId="ref2338" refString="Hatch, M. H. The Beetles of the Pacific Northwest. Part III. Pselaphidae and Diversicornia I. - Seattle: University of Washington Press, 1962. - 503 p." type="book" year="1962">Hatch, 1962</bibRefCitation>
) in the shape of pronotum and puncturation of elytra, but clearly differs in having meso- and metasternum closely and coarsely punctured, ventrite 1 densely punctured and in the shape of tibiae.
</paragraph>
